metadata_image_platform \r\n-----------------------+-------------------------\r\n emi-BFB937FB          | linux\r\n eri-98C437FB          | linux\r\n eki-63693FE4          | linux\r\n emi-B79E3832          | windows\r\n emi-7BDB441F          | windows\r\n eri-B2EA39F7          | linux\r\n emi-1CD63E15          | windows\r\n emi-1C6544D3          | windows\r\n eki-E9C83BA3          | linux\r\n emi-5FCA45D8          | linux\r\n emi-25693AEC          | linux\r\n emi-23FC43B0          | windows\r\n(12 rows)\r\n\r\nI'm trying to use Hybridfox and Rightscale to manage my instances, but neither appear to be able to see the platform field correctly, resulting in an inability to natively use RDP access to my instances through their web interfaces. \r\n\r\nI have checked the instance table directly and it appears the database shows the platform set correctly for my instances:\r\n\r\neucalyptus_cloud=# select metadata_display_name, metadata_vm_platform from metadata_instances \\g\r\n metadata_display_name | metadata_vm_platform \r\n-----------------------+----------------------\r\n i-C2A74299            | windows\r\n i-0CBA41F2            | windows\r\n i-F8A73F5A            | linux\r\n i-835C455B            | windows\r\n(4 rows)\r\n\r\nIt seems related, but if I need to create additional issues for my problems relating to Hybridfox or Rightscale please let me know. \r\n\r\nBen","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"Platform not returning for all images with euca-describe-images","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=djben","name":"djben","key":"djben","accountId":"557058:95eb3228-402c-4961-b047-8f81e3194667","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=48&d=http