nseItemType.html","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=gholms","name":"gholms","key":"gholms","accountId":"557058:6e5fdc25-c797-4d3d-8fd4-55c3c4ed99b0","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Garrett Holmstrom","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2012-08-23T17:16:48.721-0500","updated":"2012-08-23T17:16:48.721-0500"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/15326/comment/31376","id":"31376","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=djben","name":"djben","key":"djben","accountId":"557058:95eb3228-402c-4961-b047-8f81e3194667","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Ben Lavalley","active":true,"timeZone":"America/New_York"},"body":"Well, I guess this is working as intended then. \n\nIn regard to using either Hybridfox or Rightscale to recognize a Windows instance and accordingly allow password retrieval, I've named my Windows images with Windows.XXXX yet they still don't seem to be picked up as being Windows. I suspected this was because the platform wasn't reported as such with the API calls. \n\nIf anyone has any comments or advice it would be much appreciated. I know Rightscale doesn't officially support Euca 3.1 yet, but I was hoping I could at least get Hybridfox going with it. ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=djben","name":"djben","key":"djben","accountId":"557058:95eb3228-402c-4961-b047-8f81e3194667","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Ben Lavalley","active":true,"timeZone":"America/New_York"},"created":"2012-08-23T19:18:58.542-0500","updated":"2012-08-23T19:18:58.542-0500"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/15326/comment/31377","id":"31377","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=gholms","name":"gholms","key":"gholms","accountId":"557058:6e5fdc25-c797-4d3d-8fd4-55c3c4ed99b0","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Garrett Holmstrom","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"AFAIK Windows images should always show up with a {{windows}} platform, no matter if they're instance-store images or EBS images.  The thing is that you have to explicitly inform the CLC that an image happens to be a Windows image before it will recognize one as such.  For an instance-store image you do this by including \"windows\" in the bundle's name.  For an EBS image you need to do this by passing {{--kernel=windows}} to {{euca-register}}.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=gholms","name":"gholms","key":"gholms","accountId":"557058:6e5fdc25-c797-4d3d-8fd4-55c3c4ed99b0","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/3e16def22dd4a96dbe507df70f15f37f?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dgholms%26avatarId%3D18100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Garrett Holmstrom","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2012-08-23T19:34:40.202-0500","updated":"2012-08-23T19:34:40.202-0500"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/15326/comment/31390","id":"31390","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=djben","name":"djben","key":"djben","accountId":"557058:95eb3228-402c-4961-b047-8f81e3194667","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Ben Lavalley","active":true,"timeZone":"America/New_York"},"body":"Thanks, Garrett -- I didn't add the --kernel switch, it wasn't mentioned in the user guide instructions for creating Windows EBS images. I guess that explains the discrepancy with platform being reported with euca-describe-images.\r\n\r\nI found some information about Hybridfox and how it was expecting the Platform field from an instance, which lead me to believe something wasn't working right with Eucalyptus. Some related posts from two years ago on the topic:\r\n\r\nhttp://open.eucalyptus.com/forum/platform-property-not-being-set-prevents-integration-hybridfox\r\nhttp://code.google.com/p/hybridfox/issues/detail?id=17 \r\n\r\nIf Hybridfox was created specifically for Eucalyptus and it is expecting this field, it sounds like a version previous to 3.1 actually was reporting it, and the functionality has since been removed? \r\n\r\nSince the Eucalyptus API is working correctly based on the adherence to the EC2 API, I hope the Hybridfox and Rightscale teams figure out another way to recognize Windows instances running on Euca 3.1 in some way in the future. \r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=djben","name":"djben","key":"djben","accountId":"557058:95eb3228-402c-4961-b047-8f81e3194667","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d9b1f5f6d899?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fb25b1f5712a5f79ab86d